Ing '''uis''', a '''little grebe''' o '''dabchick''' king Inglis (''Tachybaptus ruficollis''), a kayabe king familiang [[grebe]] da reng ayup king danuman. Ibat ya ing lagyu ning genus king minunang Griegung ''takhus'' "mabilis" ampong ''bapto'' "lumbug king lalam". Ing lagyu ning species, a ''ruficollis'' ibat ya king [[Latin]] a ''rufus'' "malutu" ampong [[Modernung Latin]] a ''-collis'', "-maki batal a", itself ibat king Latin a ''collum'' "batal".<ref name=job>{{cite book | last= Jobling | first= James A | year= 2010| title= The Helm Dictionary of Scientific Bird Names | publisher=Christopher Helm | location = London | isbn = 978-1-4081-2501-4 | pages=341, 377}}</ref>

{{convert|23|to|29|cm|in|abbr=on}} king kaba ya ing malating diling miembru o kayanib ning kayang familia king [[Europa]]. Mayayakit ya kareng maleparan a danuman king keraklan king lugal nung nu ya mayayakit.

==Taxonomy==
Anam la reng makikilalang subspecies king salukuyan, a pikakawani da keraklan king degulan ampong kule.<ref name=Ogilvie2003/><ref name=IOC/>
* ''T. r. ruficollis'' – <small>([[Peter Simon Pallas|Pallas]], 1764)</small>: [[Nominate subspecies#Nominotypical subspecies ampong subspecies autonyms|nominate]], mayayakit ya manibat king  [[Europa]] ampong [[albugan]]g  [[Rusia]] pa[[mauli]] angga king [[pangulu]]ng [[Africa]]<ref name=Clements/>
* ''T. r. iraquensis'' – <small>([[Claud B. Ticehurst|Ticehurst]], 1923)</small>: mayayakit ya king [[mauli]]-[[aslagan]]g [[Iraq]] ampong [[mauli]]-[[albugan]]g and Iran<ref name=Clements/>
* ''T. r. capensis'' – <small>([[Tommaso Salvadori|Salvadori]], 1884)</small>: mayayakit ya king Sub-Saharan [[Africa]], [[Madagascar]], [[Sri Lanka]], ampo king  the subcontinenti ning [[India]], papunta king [[aslagan]] Burma<ref name=Clements/>
* ''T. r. poggei'' – <small>(Reichenow, 1902)</small>: mayayakit ya king [[pangulu]]-[[aslagan]]ng [[Asia]], Hainan, Taiwan, Japan, ampong [[mauli]]ng Islang Kuril <ref name=Clements/>
* ''T. r. philippensis'' – <small>(Bonnaterre, 1790)</small>: mayayakit ya king [[pangulu]]ng [[Filipinas]]<ref name=Clements/>
* ''T. r. cotabato'' – <small>([[Austin L. Rand|Rand]], 1948)</small>: mayayakit ya king [[Mindanao]]<ref name=Clements/>
